subtitleNullable: A seismogram for the 2016 Fukushima Earthquake as recorded in Matsushiro, Japan
descriptionNullable:
This data was downloaded from the [SAGE Wilber 3 dashboard](https://ds.iris.edu/wilber3/), which has downloadable seismograms from [seismic stations](https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/seismic-station) around the world.

[SAGE](https://www.iris.edu/hq/sage) is the Seismological Facility for the Advancement of Geoscience, and they have [dozens of online data tools and APIs for getting seismic data](https://ds.iris.edu/ds/nodes/dmc/tools/##).

The seismogram data is measured in [millimeters of ground displacement](https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/seismometers-seismographs-seismograms-whats-difference-how-do-they-work).

When using the data, please credit the EarthScope Consortium and see their ["How to Cite" page](https://www.earthscope.org/how-to-cite/).

Photo by [Tuan P. on Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/photos/a-view-of-a-city-with-mountains-in-the-background--OKddMFpMFA).
